<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900927-0158</DOCNO><DOCID>900927-0158.</DOCID><HL>   Notable andamp; Quotable</HL><DATE>09/27/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A18</SO><LP>   An anonymous Manhattan writer quoted in the July 7 issueof the New York Times:                                                                                                       </LP><TEXT>   &quot;If you have a plain Christmas creche, it violates theFirst Amendment to pay for it with taxpayers' money. But ifan artist submerges the entire Christmas creche in urine, itviolates the First Amendment to forbid paying for it withtaxpayers' money.&quot;</TEXT></DOC>